description:
## Problem

One unwrap() call exists in production code in src/engine/executor.rs at line 122, violating STYLE_GUIDE.md.

## Location

Line 122: `file.language.unwrap()` in execute() method

Current code:
```rust
let tree = if !ast_rules.is_empty() && file.language.is_some() {
    self.parse_ast(&content, file.language.unwrap())
} else {
    None
};
```

The unwrap is guarded by is_some() check, so it cannot panic, but it still violates the style guide.

## Proposed Solution

Use and_then combinator:
```rust
let tree = if !ast_rules.is_empty() {
    file.language.and_then(|lang| self.parse_ast(&content, lang))
} else {
    None
};
```

## Success Criteria
- No unwrap() in production code paths
- All tests pass
- cargo clippy passes
